 annotations:  *1: you need a special Falcon-patch
 ------------  *2: uses no special animation-format
               *3: overlay 2 different screens
               *4: you can show 512 colors, great function !
 
(Redax: *4 NO! You can show more than 512 colors! On STE up to 3200 at one
        picture! Up to 200 palettes with each 16 colors > 3200,but only on
        STE.)

 DPAINT:   good:     -4096 colors
 ~~~~~~~             -realtime magnify

           bad:      -very expansive
                     -loading-errors

 NEO:      good:     -raster-function
 ~~~~                -Kultprogramm

           bad:      -it bugs very often
                     -shitty text-function

 CRACKART: good:     -big format-support
 ~~~~~~~~~           -distort-options

           bad:      -you can use drawing functions in the magnify
                     -no STE support


 As you can see, every program has it's advantages and disadvantages.
 Everybody should decide by himself, what program is the best for him.



